@page "/privacypolicy"
@inject SiteConfig Config

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy - @Config.SiteName</PageTitle>

<section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container narrow reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>Last updated: May 26, 2026</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
        <div class="privacy-body reveal">

            <p>
                Mooganic Family Farm ("we," "us," or "our") operates the website located at
                <strong>mooganicfamilyfarm.com</strong> (the "Site"). This page tells you what
                information we collect, how we use it, and what rights you have. We keep it
                plain and honest because that's how we do everything around here.
            </p>

            <h2>What information we collect</h2>

            <h3>Information you give us directly</h3>
            <p>
                When you fill out our contact form, you provide your name, email address, and
                whatever message you choose to send us. We only use that information to respond
                to you. We don't add you to a mailing list without asking, and we don't sell
                or share your contact details with anyone.
            </p>

            <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
            <p>
                Like most websites, our server may log standard technical information when you
                visit — things like your IP address, browser type, pages visited, and time of
                visit. This is used only for keeping the site running and diagnosing problems.
                We do not use it to identify you personally.
            </p>

            <h3>Cookies</h3>
            <p>
                This site may use small data files called cookies to remember basic preferences
                and improve your experience. We don't use cookies to track you across other
                websites or for advertising. If your browser allows it, you can disable cookies
                at any time — the site will still work.
            </p>

            <h2>Third-party links</h2>
            <p>
                Our blog and Pinterest boards link out to other websites we like. Once you leave
                mooganicfamilyfarm.com, this privacy policy no longer applies. Pinterest has its
                own privacy policy at <strong>pinterest.com/privacy</strong>. We're not
                responsible for the practices of any site we link to.
            </p>

            <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
            <p>
                Some posts on this site may contain affiliate links, meaning we earn a small
                commission if you buy something through that link at no extra cost to you. We
                only recommend things our family has actually used and liked. Affiliate
                relationships are disclosed in the relevant posts.
            </p>

            <h2>How we use your information</h2>
            <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Respond to messages you send through the contact form</li>
                <li>Keep the website running correctly</li>
                <li>Understand how people use the site so we can improve it</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to any third party.
                Full stop.
            </p>

            <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
            <p>
                This site is a family blog and is meant for general audiences. We do not
                knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe
                a child has submitted personal information to us, please contact us and we
                will delete it promptly.
            </p>

            <h2>Your rights</h2>
            <p>
                You have the right to ask us what personal information we hold about you, to
                request its correction or deletion, and to opt out of any communications from
                us at any time. Just send us a note at the address below.
            </p>

            <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
            <p>
                We may update this policy occasionally. When we do, we'll update the date at
                the top of this page. Continuing to use the site after a change means you
                accept the updated policy.
            </p>

            <h2>Contact us</h2>
            <p>
                Questions about this policy? Reach out at
                <a href="mailto:@Config.ContactEmail">@Config.ContactEmail</a> or use the
                <a href="/contact">contact form</a>. We read everything.
            </p>

        </div>
    </div>
</section>
